<p>You absolutely need to know your birth time in order to determine your V=
ertex, as it is just as time-sensitive as the Ascendant. The Ascendant, hou=
se cusps, and points derived from these points are the most time-dependent =
factors in the birth chart. The Vertex is found closer to the Descendant th=
an the Ascendant.</p>
<p>**<strong>Please note</strong> that the Vertex, like the Ascendant, is h=
ighly sensitive to a correct time zone. While the calculator above is excel=
lent for time zones for births from 1970 onward, it=E2=80=99s missing some =
of the historical time changes. Daylight saving time, in particular, was no=
t standardized and varied greatly not only between states but often between=
 towns and cities. <em>If you were born before 1970</em>,&nbsp;check your V=
ertex with us at reports@cafeastrology.com to be certain.</p>
<p>Read about the Vertex:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://cafeastrology.com/vertex.=
html">here</a>.</p>
